re in hospital, with three in intensive care, two of whom were in a critical condition.<ref name=\"RNZ 16 April 2020\">{{cite news |title=Fifteen new cases of Covid-19 in NZ, no further deaths |url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/414389/fifteen-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-nz-no-further-deaths |accessdate=16 April 2020 |work=[[Radio New Zealand]] |date=16 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200416015053/https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/414389/fifteen-new-cases-of-covid-19-in-nz-no-further-deaths |archivedate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 April, 8 new cases (2 confirmed and 6 probable) were reported, bringing the total to 1,409 (1,086 confirmed and 323 probable), and 46 recoveries were reported, bringing the total to 816.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=17 April 2020|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200417012538/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|archive-date=17 April 2020|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref> Two further deaths were announced: a women in her eighties who was part of the Rosewood rest home cluster, and a man in his nineties who was linked to the Matamata cluster.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wade |first1=Amelia |title=Coronavirus Covid 19: Two new deaths, new details about level 3 revealed |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12325473 |access-date=17 April 2020 |work=[[New Zealand Herald]] |date=17 April 2020 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20200417023930/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id=1&objectid=12325473 |archive-date=17 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April, 13 new cases (8 confirmed and 5 probable) were reported, bringing the total to 1,422 (1,094 confirmed and 328 probabl